<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Boanerges on 03-15-2001 10:13 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Verant never ceases to amaze me... they do all kinds of good stuff and then pull this crap. 

Basically, The Warrens is the Kobold castle. Think SolB for kids. Tons of Kobolds just roaming around. I took my level 19 mage down there. Shoulda just taken my 55 cleric instead. 99% of the stuff there conned green. My roommate brought his level 14 mage and even then 80% was blue. What little did con blue was, of course, being camped. Factions were -(some new Kobold faction) +Heretic +HighCouncilofErudin (we really hate kobolds like them  ) BEWARE the new NPC in the newbie yard of Paineel. Some Necro that conned red and fear kited me (I kid you not). Paineel vets said they'd never seen him before. 

EVERYTHING gave me a message that said "*mob name* was trivial for your party" which meant I got coin and some straw armor (everyone but pure casters. Low AC, no stats). Apparently, "trivial" means green. 

First off, Verant was adamant about no new lowbie zones so I have no clue why they put this in with Tox and Kerra already in place and 10x better. It's not like Tox or Kerra are brimming with people already. Moreover, there is a need for mid range content (the 20-40 range) so this doesn't alleviate things. 

Second, this zone is THE worst designed in the game. It makes Runnyeye look fun by compare. There are whole rooms filled with mobs and if you pull one, they all come. I died twice from green waves that pecked me to death. Most people preferred the hallways on the jail side where pulling singles was easier. Chain agro is a nightmare and if it happens deep inside, you're dead. You can't run back out past all those Kobolds. And if I was getting smacked down at 19 I shudder to think what someone in the "ideal" range would go through. And to top it all off there are sentries that see invis in some areas making CR a nightmare. 

Bottom line: this was very disappointing. Verant has been making some good strides but this was a step in the wrong direction. Moreover, it goes to show they haven't learned anything from their past mistakes (Runnyeye is still broken as a mid level dungeon for the same reasons). The only reasons to go there are if you have an Erudite newbie or you need a good source for Paineel and Erudin faction (I think that was added to balance out Fear).



------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
Erudite Templar of Prexus
Cohort Chalybeius
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
